THE ATP RATED PILOT WAS TAXIING THE AIRCRAFT ON TAXIWAY 'B' TO RUNWAY 26 FOR 
TAKEOFF. HE REPORTED THAT AS HE WAS TAXIING, A GUST LIFTED THE AIRCRAFT'S TAIL. 
THE AIRCRAFT THEN NOSED OVER AND CAME TO REST INVERTED. THE PILOT REPORTED THE 
WIND WAS FROM 250 DEG WITH GUSTS TO 45 KTS. DURING THE 1516 MST WX 
OBSERVATION, THE WIND WAS FROM 280 DEG AT 30 GUSTING 45 KTS. 
IMPROPER PLANNING/DECISION BY THE PILOT.  FACTORS RELATED TO THE 
ACCIDENT WERE THE HIGH WIND AND GUSTS, WHICH HE WAS UNABLE TO 
COMPENSATE FOR. 
